description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a full-time ward receptionist to join our team within the Medicine division based on ward D55 HCOP at the Queens medical centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an organised, efficient and progressive individual who can demonstrate good interpersonal skills and effective communication talents within a multi-professional team. The successful candidate will be a vital team member who will have regular interaction with all patients and visitors to the ward. While working as part of the whole team they will need to have the capability to prioritise their own workload, be confident and adaptable to varying situations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant needs to be able to demonstrate co-operative and productive working with people of all backgrounds. They need to be experienced in the use of electronic communications and be confident during face to face interactions with patients and visitors. They will be a focal point of contact to the ward who also acts as an information resource for staff and visitors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant requires an ability to show attention to detail even under pressure while maintaining confidentiality at all times, in order to support colleagues to provide good standards of care. They need to be able to deliver accurate and clear information to appropriate parties, in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful individual will be joining a professional, developing team and will be fully supported to facilitate a smooth induction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
